Just begin typing, a sentence that begins with a . or a - is considered morse code, and will be translated to alphanumeric letters
Otherwise, the reverse will occur.

When typing morse code, use a single space inbetween characters, and two spaces inbetween words.
- is a dah
. is a dit
EX, to input the sentence "test test."
- . ... -  - . ... - .-.-.-

Supported characters a-z, A-Z, 0-9, period, and comma.